"{\"uid\": \"wnd.com-2024-08-woke-ideology-hasnt-ruined-the-olympics-yet\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"ByVictor Joecks  August 13, 2024  The things that made the Olympics so incredible are what the left wants to destroy in this country.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 133, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The closing ceremony for the 2024 Paris Olympics Games was Sunday.\", \"from\": 135, \"to\": 201, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For the past two weeks, the world's best athletes have competed for gold and greatness.\", \"from\": 202, \"to\": 289, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If past viewing patterns hold, billions of people saw some portion of these games.\", \"from\": 290, \"to\": 372, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Think about why that is.\", \"from\": 374, \"to\": 398, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Get the hottest, most important news stories on the internet - delivered FREE to your inbox as soon as they break!\", \"from\": 400, \"to\": 514, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Take just 30 seconds and sign up for WND's Email News Alerts!\", \"from\": 515, \"to\": 576, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 552, \"end\": 555, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/WorldNetDaily\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"WND\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/WorldNetDaily\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/WorldNetDaily\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One reason is that athletes do not just compete for individual glory.\", \"from\": 578, \"to\": 647, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They represent their country.\", \"from\": 648, \"to\": 677, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Last month, you probably did not know anything about swimmer Kate Douglass or 1,500 meter winner Cole Hocker.\", \"from\": 678, \"to\": 787, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 739, \"end\": 752, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Douglass\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kate Douglass\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Douglass\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Douglass\"}, {\"begin\": 775, \"end\": 786, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cole_Hocker\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Cole Hocker\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cole_Hocker\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cole_Hocker\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"You may not even understand the rules of fencing or rugby, but that did not matter.\", \"from\": 788, \"to\": 871, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You knew those athletes wore the red, white and blue, and that was reason enough to cheer them on.\", \"from\": 872, \"to\": 970, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Personally, I loved hearing my kids spontaneously chant \\\"USA, USA, USA\\\" as they watched Katie Ledecky swim to victory.\", \"from\": 972, \"to\": 1090, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1029, \"end\": 1032, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999997903615, \"rank\": 2.0660778478402638e-10, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1034, \"end\": 1037, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999997903615, \"rank\": 2.0660778478402638e-10, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1039, \"end\": 1042, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999997903615, \"rank\": 2.0660778478402638e-10, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1060, \"end\": 1073, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katie Ledecky\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"National pride is a natural human emotion.\", \"from\": 1092, \"to\": 1134, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1092, \"end\": 1106, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patriotism\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"National pride\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patriotism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patriotism\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the women's 100-meter dash, Julien Alfred won Saint Lucia's first ever gold medal.\", \"from\": 1135, \"to\": 1220, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1184, \"end\": 1195, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Lucia\", \"score\": 0.9999999984011083, \"rank\": 1.5692254276129035e-09, \"text\": \"Saint Lucia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Lucia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Lucia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The country erupted in celebration.\", \"from\": 1221, \"to\": 1256, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Her victory was their victory.\", \"from\": 1257, \"to\": 1287, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's a vivid example that people are not like atoms that randomly bump into each other.\", \"from\": 1289, \"to\": 1376, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We crave and need connection - in a family, local community and a country.\", \"from\": 1377, \"to\": 1451, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Generally, it's good to be proud of your country.\", \"from\": 1453, \"to\": 1502, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Further, the U.S. is a country worth being proud of.\", \"from\": 1503, \"to\": 1555, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"When victorious U.S. athletes draped the flag over their shoulders, like 400-meter hurdles champion Sydney McLaughlin-Levrone, they beamed.\", \"from\": 1556, \"to\": 1695, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1656, \"end\": 1662, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.9999914236486228, \"rank\": 8.559893266381996e-06, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"What a contrast to the left's push to kneel for the national anthem just a few years ago or smearing the country as systemically racist.\", \"from\": 1697, \"to\": 1833, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympics are the ultimate competitive stage.\", \"from\": 1835, \"to\": 1883, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The point is to provide a level playing field and see who comes out on top.\", \"from\": 1884, \"to\": 1959, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That's equality.\", \"from\": 1960, \"to\": 1976, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The diversity, equity and inclusion crowd does not want that.\", \"from\": 1977, \"to\": 2038, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Equitable treatment means we all end up at the same place,\\\" Democrat presidential nominee and Vice President Kamala Harris has said.\", \"from\": 2040, \"to\": 2173, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2101, \"end\": 2109, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California_Democratic_Party\", \"score\": 0.9964880423007588, \"rank\": 0.0016136712533176129, \"text\": \"Democrat\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California_Democratic_Party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California_Democratic_Party\"}, {\"begin\": 2150, \"end\": 2156, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kamala_Harris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999849933, \"rank\": 1.513128993037566e-11, \"text\": \"Kamala\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kamala_Harris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kamala_Harris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Think about how absurd this is.\", \"from\": 2175, \"to\": 2206, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Officials would have to punish Simone Biles for being the greatest female gymnast of all time.\", \"from\": 2207, \"to\": 2301, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2238, \"end\": 2250, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Simone Biles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That's the only way to put her in the same place as her peers.\", \"from\": 2302, \"to\": 2364, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That would obviously be unfair, but it's analogous to what the left wants the government to do.\", \"from\": 2365, \"to\": 2460, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A broader version of this argument would apply that standard to groups.\", \"from\": 2462, \"to\": 2533, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The government, the left would say, needs to give special advantages to certain racial minorities.\", \"from\": 2534, \"to\": 2632, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Think about how this would work at the Olympics.\", \"from\": 2634, \"to\": 2682, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The U.S. won 126 medals.\", \"from\": 2683, \"to\": 2707, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"India won just six.\", \"from\": 2708, \"to\": 2727, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2708, \"end\": 2713, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"score\": 0.9989313122107738, \"rank\": 0.0006132538355746344, \"text\": \"India\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The U.S. population is around 337 million.\", \"from\": 2728, \"to\": 2770, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"India's is more than 1.45 billion.\", \"from\": 2771, \"to\": 2805, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2771, \"end\": 2776, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"score\": 0.9989313122107738, \"rank\": 0.0006132538355746344, \"text\": \"India\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The disproportionate result is obvious.\", \"from\": 2806, \"to\": 2845, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"India has more than four times as many people, but the U.S. won 20 times more medals.\", \"from\": 2846, \"to\": 2931, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2846, \"end\": 2851, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"score\": 0.9989313122107738, \"rank\": 0.0006132538355746344, \"text\": \"India\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But to even that out would require taking medals away from deserving U.S. athletes.\", \"from\": 2933, \"to\": 3016, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sorry, Noah Lyles.\", \"from\": 3017, \"to\": 3035, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sure, you won the 100 meters in a literal photo finish, but your country has won too many medals.\", \"from\": 3036, \"to\": 3133, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Your gold needs to go to someone else.\", \"from\": 3134, \"to\": 3172, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The injustice would be obvious.\", \"from\": 3173, \"to\": 3204, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That's analogous to what affirmative action and other DEI initiatives do.\", \"from\": 3205, \"to\": 3278, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Perhaps that's fine in sports, a leftist might counter, but in real life, the government still needs to step in to help people succeed.\", \"from\": 3280, \"to\": 3415, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Here's the problem with that argument: Competition makes you work harder.\", \"from\": 3416, \"to\": 3489, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That makes you better, even if you do not come out on top.\", \"from\": 3490, \"to\": 3548, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympics are a zero-sum game, but in a free market, the economy is not.\", \"from\": 3549, \"to\": 3624, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If you work hard, you will succeed even if you are not the top in your field.\", \"from\": 3625, \"to\": 3702, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Shoot, I am not even the best conservative columnist named Victor.\", \"from\": 3704, \"to\": 3770, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3763, \"end\": 3769, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RCA_Records\", \"score\": 0.6662937495062093, \"rank\": 0.484633638403855, \"text\": \"Victor\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q18127\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RCA_Records\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RCA_Records\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But I'd like to think practice has improved my writing over the years.\", \"from\": 3771, \"to\": 3841, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The left's woke ideology would not just ruin the Olympics.\", \"from\": 3843, \"to\": 3901, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It would ruin America.\", \"from\": 3902, \"to\": 3924, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"SUPPORT TRUTHFUL JOURNALISM.\", \"from\": 3926, \"to\": 3954, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"MAKE A DONATION TO THE NONPROFIT WND NEWS CENTER.\", \"from\": 3955, \"to\": 4004, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"THANK YOU!\", \"from\": 4005, \"to\": 4015, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Victor Joecks is a columnist for the Las Vegas Review-Journal.\", \"from\": 4017, \"to\": 4079, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4017, \"end\": 4023, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RCA_Records\", \"score\": 0.6662937495062093, \"rank\": 0.484633638403855, \"text\": \"Victor\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q18127\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RCA_Records\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RCA_Records\"}, {\"begin\": 4054, \"end\": 4078, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Las_Vegas_Review-Journal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Las Vegas Review-Journal\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Las_Vegas_Review-Journal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Las_Vegas_Review-Journal\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Email him at[email\\u00a0protected]or follow @victorjoecks on X.Read more of Victor Joecks's articles here.\", \"from\": 4080, \"to\": 4181, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4151, \"end\": 4157, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RCA_Records\", \"score\": 0.6662937495062093, \"rank\": 0.484633638403855, \"text\": \"Victor\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q18127\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RCA_Records\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RCA_Records\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"You must belogged into post a comment.\", \"from\": 4183, \"to\": 4221, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"About us  Subscribe  Go Ad-Free  Privacy policy  Copyright \\u00a9 2026 WorldNetDaily  Copyright \\u00a9 2026 WorldNetDaily  March 22, 2026  Joe Kovacs  March 22, 2026  Joe Kovacs  March 22, 2026  RealClearWire\", \"from\": 4223, \"to\": 4421, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4352, \"end\": 4355, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joe_DiMaggio\", \"score\": 0.7391439756343896, \"rank\": 0.3529134869139218, \"text\": \"Joe\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joe_DiMaggio\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joe_DiMaggio\"}, {\"begin\": 4380, \"end\": 4383, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joe_DiMaggio\", \"score\": 0.7391439756343896, \"rank\": 0.3529134869139218, \"text\": \"Joe\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joe_DiMaggio\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joe_DiMaggio\"}]}]}"